Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesson 19 The stuff of dreams\N\N话梦话的本质\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.37,0:00:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is going on when a person experiences rapid eye-movements during sleep?\N\N当一个人在睡眠中突然有眼部活动时,什么事情正在发生?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.24,0:00:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It is fairly clear that the sleeping period must have some function,\N\N很清楚,睡眠必然具有某种作用.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.93,0:00:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and because there is so much of it the function would seem to be important.\N\N睡眠占去那么多时间,所以其作用似乎还很重要.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.03,0:00:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Speculations about its nature have been going on for literally thousands of years,\N\N人们对睡眠作用的种种猜测,确实已有数千年之久.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.90,0:00:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and one odd finding that makes the problem puzzling\N\N一项使人对这个问题感到困惑的奇怪的,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.45,0:00:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it looks very much as if sleeping is not simply a matter of giving the body a rest.\N\N发现是,睡眠在很大程度似乎并不仅仅是为了使身体得到休息.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,'Rest',in terms of muscle relaxation and so on,\N\N"休息",从使肌肉得到放松等方面来看,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.23,0:00:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,can be achieved by a brief period lying,or even sitting down.\N\N只要稍微躺一躺,甚至坐一坐就能达到.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.48,0:01:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,tissue: n.  组织\N\NThe body's tissues are self-repairing and self-restoring to a degree,\N\N人体组织在一定程度上有自我修补和自我恢复的能力,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.76,0:01:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and function best when more or less continuously active.\N\N有张有弛地连续活动时,其功能最佳.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.89,0:01:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact a basic amount of movement occurs during sleep\N\N事实上,睡眠状态下仍有着基本的活动量,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.85,0:01:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which is specifically concerned with preventing muscle inactivity.\N\N以防止肌肉活动停止.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.21,0:01:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is not a question of resting the body,\N\N如果睡眠的功能不是在于使身体得到休息,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.17,0:01:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then perhaps it is the brain that needs resting?\N\N那么也许是让大脑得以休息?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.42,0:01:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothesis: n.  假说\N\NThis might be a plausible hypothesis were it not for two factors.\N\N若不是下面两点,这种假设似乎是有道理的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.05,0:01:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,electroencephalograph: n.  脑电图仪\N\NFirst the electroencephalograph,\N\N第一点,脑电图记录仪，\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.64,0:01:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which is simply a device for recording the electrical activity of the brain\N\N(不过是一种记录脑电活动的仪器）\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.17,0:01:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,electrode: n.  电极, scalp: n.  头皮\N\Nby attaching electrodes to the scalp)\N\N方法是通过把电极接到头皮上来记录.)\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.84,0:01:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,shows that while there is a change in the pattern of activity during sleep,\N\N显示人在睡眠时大脑活动的方式有变化,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.51,0:01:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no evidence that the total amount of activity is any less.\N\N但没有迹象表明,其活动总量有任何减少.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.77,0:01:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The second factor is more interesting and more fundamental.\N\N第二点更有意思,也更重要.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.89,0:02:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist: n.  精神病学家\N\NSome years ago an American psychiatrist named William Dement published experiments,\N\N前些年,美国一位名叫威廉.迪蒙特的精神病学者发表了一个报告,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.54,0:02:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,dealing with the recording of eye-movements during sleep.\N\N报告中记录了眼球在睡眠时的活动情况.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.74,0:02:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He showed that the average individual's sleep cycle\N\N他指出,平常人的睡眠周期中\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.12,0:02:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,punctuate: v.  不时介入\N\Nis punctuated with peculiar bursts of eye-movements,\N\N不时伴有一阵阵奇怪的眼球活动,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.05,0:02:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,some drifting and slow,others jerky and rapid.\N\N这些活动有的飘忽而缓慢,有的急剧而快速.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.22,0:02:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,People woken during these periods of eye-movements,\N\N在眼球活动期间被叫醒的人，\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.08,0:02:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,generally reported that they had been dreaming.\N\N都说自己在做梦;\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.33,0:02:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When woken at other times they reported no dreams.\N\N在其他期间叫醒他们,则说没做梦.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.76,0:02:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If one group of people,\N\N如果有一组人，\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,were disturbed from their eye-movement sleep for several nights on end,\N\N连续几夜在眼球活动时被叫醒,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and another group were disturbed for an equal period of time\N\N另一组人也是连续几夜被叫醒,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.90,0:02:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but when they were not exhibiting eye-movements,\N\N但是在眼球没活动时被叫醒的,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.75,0:02:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,disorder: n.  失调\N\Nthe first group began to show some personality disorders\N\N结果,第一组人开始出现性格失常,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.67,0:02:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,while the others seemed more or less unaffected.\N\N而第二组人似乎没受什么影响.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.70,0:02:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,implication: n.  表明\N\NThe implications of all this were that\N\N这一切暗示我们:\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.97,0:02:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it was not the disturbance of sleep that mattered,\N\N睡眠受到干扰没关系,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:03:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but the disturbance of dreaming.\N\N而做梦受到干扰是有问题的.\N\N